&lt;p&gt;Here's a brief explanation:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;research&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;write_todos&lt;/code&gt; are expandable, clicking reveals the full query + findings or the live todo checklist with &lt;code&gt;pending&lt;/code&gt; / &lt;code&gt;inprogress&lt;/code&gt; / &lt;code&gt;completed&lt;/code&gt; states.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;resultSummary&lt;/code&gt; appears as a small green line below the display text so you can glance at the output without expanding.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;DefaultToolCard&lt;/code&gt; handles any tool not in &lt;code&gt;TOOL_CONFIG&lt;/code&gt;, showing collapsible args and result JSON.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In this component, &lt;code&gt;ExpandedDetails&lt;/code&gt; handles the per-tool expanded view. &lt;code&gt;research&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;write_todos&lt;/code&gt; get structured layouts; everything else falls back to a JSON pre block.&lt;br&gt;
